cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for face detection, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel multi-branch fully convolutional network architecture, which involves training deep neural networks, and thus it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional feature maps, which are commonly used in multimedia processing, suggesting that it could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which could be related to optimization techniques in neural networks, and thus it could also be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
